                                         JOHANNESBURG - Limpopo police are searching for a lion that escaped from a trailer outside Tzaneen.  It’s understood that two of the big cats jumped off the trailer on Sunday but one of them was recaptured after it was injured. The police's Moatshe Ngoepe says a search is underway for the other one. “If a lion is on the loose, the lives of our people might be in danger. Let them pay extra care whenever they are moving around the area but on the same note, when they see it, let them immediately contact the nearest police station.”